description.narrative: ACO continued to demonstrate a gender commitment to programming for better results across Afghanistan Country Office's priority areas of intervention, and provided a special focus in programming on the following targeted priorities: child marriage, violence against women and girls, girls' education, adolescent nutrition and menstrual hygiene management, including during Covid- 19 pandemic response. The office engaged in strategic partnership with selected women CSOs for increased targeted access to hard-to-reach women and girls on COVID-19 prevention and response, which accelerated improvement in awareness to this group, who are otherwise missed with regular channels for awareness raising. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/07/2020
